<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Flywheel and Housing - Installation of Flywheel
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Installation of Flywheel</title>
        <figure id="f1200708" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Flywheel</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel and Ring Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Guide Studs</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two flywheel guide studs into the 3 o'clock and 9 o'clock positions of the
                crankshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the flywheel over the guide studs. Secure the flywheel to the crankshaft with eight
                mounting bolts finger tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For automatic transmissions, install the flywheel adapter, flexplate and reinforcement ring. Make
                    sure the lip of the ring is facing outward. Then install the eight mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two guide studs and install the remaining two mounting bolts. Tighten all ten
                bolts to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
